               <head>Hazin, biography</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85014157 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010105563 http://lccn.loc.gov/n88646608 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010106697" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4036-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Title not stated</p>
                        <p>An anonymous, brief biography of the Persian poet and writer, Muḥammad ʿAlī Lāhijī "Ḥazīn," based on the author's family narratives and access to the poet's autograph manuscript, subsequently stolen at Lucknow</p>
                        <p>According to the scribe's comments noted by William Irvine (f. 1r), the author of this anonymous work is Mīrzā Muḥammad Ṣādiq, a relation of Fayz̤ Allāh Bayg, the muṣāḥib (companion) of Rājah Chayt Singh, Mīrzā Kalb ʿAlī Bayg, and Babr al-Mulk</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Transcribed by order of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="fmo">G. J. Nicholls</persName>, Judge at <name type="place">Farrukhabad</name>, from a manuscript obtained from <name type="place">Agra</name>
                     </note>
                     <filiation>Copied by order of Mr Roberts, Commissioner and Agent to the Governor, Benares Division, from a manuscript found in Benares</filiation>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
